1e:["$","p","p-9",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Why it survives:"}]," Funding rates exist because perpetual futures need a mechanism to track spot prices. This mechanism doesn't stop in bear markets — it reverses direction. In bull markets, longs pay shorts. In bear markets, shorts pay longs."]}]
1f:["$","p","p-10",{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"className":"text-foreground font-semibold","children":"Why it can thrive:"}]," Different exchanges respond to market pressure at different speeds. When panic hits, Binance funding might go to -30% annualized while Hyperliquid is still at +5% on the same pair. That's a 35% spread. Volatility increases dispersion, and dispersion is what cross-exchange arbitrage captures."]}]
